## Play with Orders

![images](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/frnmjn/es-cqrs-anatomy/main/img/Linus-Torvalds-quote-about-talking-2a9797.jpg)

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

Let's create an Order invoking the relative command and take the aggregate id from the command response, for the next steps.

<!-- livebook:{"attrs":"","chunks":null,"kind":"Elixir.Kino.RemoteExecutionCell","livebook_object":"smart_cell"} -->

```elixir
require Kino.RPC
node = :escqrsanatomy@escqrsanatomy
Node.set_cookie(node, String.to_atom(System.fetch_env!("LB_COOKIE")))

aggregate_uuid =
  Kino.RPC.eval_string(
    node,
    ~S"""
    alias EsCqrsAnatomy.Order.Commands.CreateOrder

    %CreateOrder{
      id: UUID.uuid4(), 
      order_number: Enum.random(1..99999) |> Integer.to_string(), 
      business_partner: "mario.rossi@google.com"
    } 
    |> EsCqrsAnatomy.App.dispatch(include_execution_result: true)
    |> elem(1)
    |> Map.get(:aggregate_uuid)
    """,
    file: __ENV__.file
  )
```

Create a connection to the Event Store

<!-- livebook:{"attrs":"eyJkYXRhYmFzZSI6ImV2ZW50X3N0b3JlIiwiaG9zdG5hbWUiOiJwb3N0Z3JlcyIsInBhc3N3b3JkIjoicG9zdGdyZXMiLCJwb3J0Ijo1NDMyLCJ0eXBlIjoicG9zdGdyZXMiLCJ1c2VfaXB2NiI6ZmFsc2UsInVzZV9zc2wiOmZhbHNlLCJ1c2VybmFtZSI6InBvc3RncmVzIiwidmFyaWFibGUiOiJjb25uX2VzIn0","chunks":null,"kind":"Elixir.KinoDB.ConnectionCell","livebook_object":"smart_cell"} -->

```elixir
opts = [
  hostname: "postgres",
  port: 5432,
  username: "postgres",
  password: "postgres",
  database: "event_store"
]

{:ok, conn_es} = Kino.start_child({Postgrex, opts})
```

Fetch all the event of the Aggregate.  
Here we **cheat a bit** using the event payload to identify all the events related to our Aggregate.  
We see the corect way to doi it soon

<!-- livebook:{"attrs":"","chunks":null,"kind":"Elixir.KinoDB.SQLCell","livebook_object":"smart_cell"} -->

```elixir
result_events =
  Postgrex.query!(
    conn_es,
    """
    SELECT 
      event_id::text,
      event_type,
      data
    FROM events 
    WHERE encode(data, 'escape')::json ->> 'id' = $1
    """,
    [aggregate_uuid]
  )
```

Every Aggregate as it's own **Stream**

<!-- livebook:{"attrs":"","chunks":null,"kind":"Elixir.KinoDB.SQLCell","livebook_object":"smart_cell"} -->

```elixir
result =
  Postgrex.query!(
    conn_es,
    """
    SELECT 
      stream_id,
      stream_uuid,
      stream_version 
    FROM streams 
    WHERE stream_uuid = $1
    """,
    [aggregate_uuid]
  )
```

